           		  <div class="dotWrap">
           		    <h1>Logo Design </h1>
       		    </div>
                	<div class="dots"></div>
              </div>
                <p><img src="images/jonny.jpg" alt="Jonny Pink - Logo Designer" width="59" height="64" align="left" class="picHomepage" />Jonny Pink is a creative consultant &amp; graphic designer who specialises in logo design and corporate branded materials such as brochures, business stationery &amp; websites.</p>
      <p>He has worked on a diverse range of  projects over the last 15 years and  has a depth of experience in producing clean &amp; simple logo design solutions that directly benefit businesses.</p>
      <p>His client list spans the globe, and includes an eclectic mix of brands and organisations from multinationals to startups to charities.</p>
                <p>If you are in need of a logo designer, or have a graphic design project that requires attention please don't hesitate to get in touch.</p>
   	</div>
                <!-- Graphic Design -->
            <div id="col2">
           	  <div class="heading">
               	<div class="dots"></div>
                		<div class="dotWrap">
                		  <h1>Graphic Designer Vs Agency</h1>
           		</div>
                	<div class="dots"></div>
                </div>
                <p>Good graphic design is all about communication. And good communication equals good design!</p>
              <p>By working directly with a designer rather than an account handler it enables  clear communication between client &amp; designer, and that really influences  the success of a project.</p>
              <p>Whilst the majority of clients initially discover Jonny when looking for a new logo, they typically stay in touch over the years and use  as a base for all their future graphic design needs.</p>
              <p>And with the flexibility of collaboration, this means the full range of abilities of a larger design agency, with all the benefits of a more intimate and cost effective service.</p>
    </div>
                
